  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>· Preparation and following up on progress claims, progress certification, variation orders and</p>\n<p>settlement of final account with main contractors, sub-contractors and suppliers</p>\n<p>· Maintain records, tracking and submission of all variation orders</p>\n<p>· Able to work closely with whole tender team and carry out management’s direction</p>\n<p>· Attend meetings/ site meetings</p>\n<p>· Work closely with teammates</p>\n<p>· Perform, any other ad-hoc duties as assigned</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>:</p>\n<p>· Able to work under minimal supervision and be meticulous</p>\n<p>· Good communication and negotiation skills</p>\n<p>· Pro-active, a good team player and able to work well under pressure</p>\n<p>· Candidate must possess Diploma/ Degree in Quantity Surveying, Civil Engineering or Building</p>\n<p>· Minimum 1 years of working experience in local Building industry</p>\n<p>· Good communication skills in English and Mandarin (to liaise with mandarin speaking associate)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Salary will be commensurate with qualification and experience</strong></p>",
